                             <h2><a href="http://texascitycomputerrepair.com/my-new-career/">My New Career</a></h2>
                           	
            <div class="entry-content">
            			
               <p>I love computers and want to start my own computer shop. The only question that I have is whether I should quit my current high-paying job and do it. The majority of my work would probably be computer repairs but I also enjoy building computers from scratch and will hope to sell them in my shop.</p>
<blockquote><p>Want to cover things in more detail? Read my last post about <a href="http://texascitycomputerrepair.com/what-is-required-for-you-to-become-a-computer-technician/">how canÂ I become a computer repair technician</a></p></blockquote>
<p>Building and selling your own computers is a brave adventure because there are so many competitors such as RadioShack, Walmart, Dell, and so forth. To make it successful is best to provide specially computers that have capabilities that the run-of-the-mill computers do not have.</p>
